            <title>[MATH-1141] UniformIntegerDistribution should make constructer a exclusive bound or made parameter check more relax</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-1141</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;UniformIntegerDistribution constructer  public UniformIntegerDistribution(RandomGenerator rng,&lt;br/&gt;
                                      int lower,&lt;br/&gt;
                                      int upper) &lt;br/&gt;
the lower and the upper all inclusive. but the parameter check made a   if (lower &amp;gt;= upper) {&lt;br/&gt;
            throw new NumberIsTooLargeException(&lt;br/&gt;
                            LocalizedFormats.LOWER_BOUND_NOT_BELOW_UPPER_BOUND,&lt;br/&gt;
                            lower, upper, false);&lt;br/&gt;
check, i think it is too strict&lt;br/&gt;
to construct UniformIntegerDistribution (0,0) &lt;br/&gt;
this should make it possible&lt;/p&gt;</description>
